<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-02T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-02T10:00:00-05:00" n="500" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/2833: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-02T09:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                        1921—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 5:18
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>128. The President’s private secretary Aguirre Muñoz leaves to-day on
                            special mission to assure Nicaraguan Government that Honduranean
                            Government will make every effort to prevent further disturbances on the
                            frontier.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>